eers, this will break downstream code.\n\nFix: Add `TargetCapabilities` to the re-export list.\n\n---\n\n**Issue 2: Misleading error message for wrong-length routing key in `decode_txt`**\nConfidence: **90**\n\nFile: `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-discovery/src/txt.rs` line 66\n\n```rust\n.map_err(|_| TxtError::InvalidRoutingKey(format!(\"expected 16 bytes, got {rk_str}\")))?;\n```\n\n`rk_str` is the hex-encoded string from the TXT record (e.g., `\"0000000000000000\"` for 8 zero bytes). The error message says \"expected 16 bytes, got 0000000000000000\" which is confusing because the hex string length is not the byte count. A reader debugging a parse failure would expect to see the actual decoded byte count (e.g., `\"expected 16 bytes, got 8\"`).\n\nThe test at line 182 uses `matches!(err, TxtError::InvalidRoutingKey(_))` and therefore doesn't catch this - the bad message passes testing silently.\n\nFix:\n```rust\n.map_err(|v: Vec<u8>| TxtError::InvalidRoutingKey(\n    format!(\"expected 16 bytes, got {}\", v.len())\n))?;\n```\n\n---\n\n**Issue 3: `bitflags` not a workspace dependency**\nConfidence: **85**\n\nFile: `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-transport/Cargo.toml` line 15\n\n```toml\nbitflags = \"2\"\n```\n\nThe workspace `Cargo.toml` does not declare `bitflags` as a workspace dependency (it doesn't appear in `[workspace.dependencies]` at all), so this crate pins it independently with a floating major version. All other direct dependencies in the workspace use `workspace = true` or are pinned precisely. This breaks the project's convention for centralized dependency management and risks version skew if another crate later adds `bitflags` independently. Since this is a new explicit dependency added by this PR, it should be managed through the workspace.\n\nFix: Add `bitflags = \"^2\"` to `[workspace.dependencies]` in the root `Cargo.toml`, then change the `reme-transport` entry to `bitflags = { workspace = true }`.\n\n---\n\n### Minor Issues (below reporting threshold but worth noting)\n\n**Unused `tracing` dependency in `reme-discovery`**\n\nFile: `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-discovery/Cargo.toml` line 14\n\n`tracing` is listed as a dependency but is not used anywhere in any of the three source files (`lib.rs`, `backend.rs`, `types.rs`, `txt.rs`). No `use tracing` or `tracing::` call exists. With workspace lints including `clippy::all`, this will surface as a warning (and the workspace lint config treats warnings as... warnings, not errors, so this won't block a build, but it is dead weight). Confidence: 75 (below threshold but worth a cleanup).\n\n**`subscribe` returning a plain `mpsc::Receiver` instead of `mpsc::UnboundedReceiver` or a wrapper**\n\nFile: `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-discovery/src/backend.rs` line 25\n\nThe `subscribe` method returns `mpsc::Receiver<DiscoveryEvent>` (bounded channel). This requires the implementor to choose a buffer size internally, but the trait gives callers no visibility into that choice and no way to configure it. The rest of the transport layer uses `mpsc::UnboundedReceiver` for event channels (see `EventReceiver` in `lib.rs`). This is a design inconsistency, not a bug per se, but it means a slow subscriber can cause the backend to block when broadcasting to multiple subscribers if the buffer fills. Confidence: 70 (below threshold, and there's only one subscriber expected per backend).\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| # | File | Issue | Confidence |\n|---|------|-------|------------|\n| 1 | `reme-transport/src/lib.rs:47` | `TargetCapabilities` missing from crate re-exports | 95 |\n| 2 | `reme-discovery/src/txt.rs:66` | Error message embeds hex string instead of byte count | 90 |\n| 3 | `reme-transport/Cargo.toml:15` | `bitflags` not a workspace dependency | 85 |\n\nThe core logic of both additions is sound: the `DiscoveryBackend` trait design is clean, `TxtError` variants are appropriate, the round-trip is tested thoroughly, and the `TargetCapabilities` bitflag values and defaults are correct. Issues 1 and 2 are the most important to fix before this is consumed by any other crate.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>45684</total_tokens><tool_uses>41</tool_uses><duration_ms>116466</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/872f27a1-9c0c-45e4-b6a3-3674f486326d/tasks/a76ee270dcbaaa796.output",
